{
  "id": "ce216aa2b8874da280b82b92c855104f",
  "title": "Physics Based Side Scroller Camera",
  "description": "Collision-based camera system including room transitions. Works for any number and shape of rooms, with a single camera.",
  "longDescription": "<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/oa_k1DclSak\" rel=\"nofollow\">VIDEO</a></p><p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/a5Y_FKNyBI0\" rel=\"nofollow\">TUTORIAL</a></p><p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Ektb9swRhXnSeEeRl-yHALrPI1y0MfbCN8uJOZpGjWA/edit?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">DOCUMENTATION</a></p><p><a href=\"https://github.com/PendingKill/SideScrollerCameraSampleProject\" rel=\"nofollow\">SAMPLE PROJECT</a></p><p><br /></p><p>This plugin provides a complete sidescroller camera system based on collision probes and blocking volumes. If the player goes near a wall and the probe hits a blocking volume, the camera stops moving any further, preventing the player from seeing beyond the room’s boundaries.</p><p><br /></p><p>Fully customizable:</p><ul><li>Rooms of any size and shape (i.e. non-rectangular rooms, sloping ceilings, hilly terrain). Not just boxes.</li><li>Collision distances in each direction</li><li>Collision channel</li><li>Camera offset</li><li>Distance from the character to the camera</li><li>Camera Lag and Camera Lag Speed</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Also includes transitions with two varieties. Simply place our custom TransitionVolume and choose:</p><ul><li>Panning: camera follows the player as they travel between rooms.</li><li>Fading: camera will fade out as the player hits the entry point, and gets teleported to the exit. You can use horizontal, vertical, even diagonal orientations.</li><li>Transition logic is written in Blueprints for easy customization.</li></ul>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>Features:</p><ul><li> 2.5D Support, including projects based on the Side Scroller template (Note: character must traverse along Y and Z axes. Paper2D is currently not supported)</li><li> Block cameras using standard Camera Blocking Volumes</li><li> Place blocking volumes in any configuration</li><li>Adjustable camera transitions between rooms</li><li>Adjustable camera lag</li><li>Customize parameters in Blueprints</li></ul><p>Code Modules:</p><ul><li> SideScrollerDynamicCamera [Runtime]</li></ul><p>Number of Blueprints: 2</p><p>Number of C&#43;&#43; Classes: 1</p><p>Network Replicated: No</p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Win32, Win64, MacOS, Linux</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: Win32, Win64, MacOS, Linux, Android</p><p>Documentation: <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Ektb9swRhXnSeEeRl-yHALrPI1y0MfbCN8uJOZpGjWA/edit?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">Docs Link</a>, <a href=\"https://youtu.be/a5Y_FKNyBI0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Video Link</a></p><p>Support: pendingkillgames&#64;gmail.com</p><p>Example Project: <a href=\"https://github.com/PendingKill/SideScrollerCameraSampleProject\" rel=\"nofollow\">GitHub Link</a></p><p>Important/Additional Notes: Character must traverse along Y and Z axes. Paper2D is currently not supported.</p><p>If migrating a UE4 project to UE5, reset the SideScrollerCameraActorchild actor in your character class by clearing the child actor class, compiling, then setting it back to SideScrollerCameraActor. There is a bug when migrating that will offset the camera from the character unless you reset the child actor.</p>",
